{"FORGATHER":[{"def":"To convene; to gossip; to meet accidentally.","pos":""}],"FORGAVE":[{"def":"For*gave\", Defn: imp.","pos":""}],"FORGE":[{"def":"A place or establishment where iron or other metals are wrought by heating and hammering; especially, a furnace, or a shop with its furnace, etc.","pos":""},{"def":"The works where wrought iron is produced directly from the ore, or where iron is rendered malleable by puddling and shingling; a shingling mill.","pos":""}],"FORGEMAN":[{"def":"A skilled smith, who has a hammerer to assist him.","pos":""}],"FORGER":[{"def":"One who forges, makes, of forms; a fabricator; a falsifier.","pos":"noun"}],"FORGERY":[{"def":"The act of forging metal into shape.","pos":""},{"def":"The act of forging, fabricating, or producing falsely; esp.","pos":""}],"FORGET":[{"def":"To lose the remembrance of; to let go from the memory; to cease to have in mind; not to think of; also, to lose the power of; to cease from doing.","pos":""},{"def":"Let y right hand forget her cunning.","pos":""}],"FORGET-ME-NOT":[{"def":"A small herb, of the genus Myosotis (M.","pos":""}],"FORGETFUL":[{"def":"Apt to forget; easily losing remembrance; as, a forgetful man should use helps to strengthen his memory.","pos":""},{"def":"Heedless; careless; neglectful; inattentive.","pos":""}],"FORGETFULLY":[{"def":"In a forgetful manner.","pos":""}],"FORGETFULNESS":[{"def":"The quality of being forgetful; prononess to let slip from the mind.","pos":""},{"def":"Loss of remembrance or recollection; a ceasing to remember; oblivion.","pos":""}],"FORGETIVE":[{"def":"Inventive; productive; capable.","pos":""}],"FORGETTABLE":[{"def":"Liable to be, or that may be, forgotten.","pos":""}],"FORGETTER":[{"def":"One who forgets; a heedless person.","pos":""}],"FORGING":[{"def":"A piece of forged work in metal; -- a general name for a piece of hammered iron or steel.","pos":""}],"FORGIVABLE":[{"def":"Capable of being forgiven; pardonable; venial.","pos":""}],"FORGIVE":[{"def":"To give wholly; to make over without reservation; to resign.","pos":""},{"def":"To give up resentment or claim to requital on account of (an offense or wrong); to remit the penalty of; to pardon; -- said in reference to the act forgiven.","pos":""}],"FORGIVENESS":[{"def":"The act of forgiving; the state of being forgiven; as, the forgiveness of sin or of injuries.","pos":""},{"def":"Disposition to pardon; willingness to forgive.","pos":""}],"FORGIVER":[{"def":"One who forgives.","pos":""}],"FORGIVING":[{"def":"Disposed to forgive; inclined to overlook offenses; mild; merciful; compassionate; placable; as, a forgiving temper.","pos":""}],"FORGO":[{"def":"To pass by; to leave.","pos":""}],"FORGOT":[{"def":"For*got\", Defn: imp.","pos":""}],"FORGOTTEN":[{"def":"For*got\"ten, Defn: p.","pos":""}]}